data.description: Welcome to Lake of the Rockies!  This better-than-new family home offers 4,318 sq feet, 4 bedrooms on the same level, 3 baths, & 3 car garage.  Bring your paddleboards & kayaks as this home is just a 5 minute walk from Monument Lake!  Want to be near downtown Monument?  This home is just a 10 minute from walk from restaurants, taprooms, the farmer's market, shops, & the largest 4th of July parade in the state!  The main level of this home has been upgraded w/hand-scraped hardwood flooring throughout and features a formal living/office/flex space that is pre-plumbed for a wet-bar/coffee bar, large family room w/gas fireplace and built-ins, gourmet kitchen w/butlers pantry and walk-in pantry, casual dining space, & keeping room for your morning coffee.  The gourmet kitchen features granite counters, oversized custom cedar-wrapped island, double ovens, gas range, and upgraded cabinetry w/pull-outs, mixer lift, and more! Stylish half bath with reclaimed lumber accent-wall and designer faucet and hardware, and tidy mudroom with built-in cabinetry complete the main level.  Upstairs you will find 4 bedrooms, 2 baths, and a large laundry room.  The spacious master suite features a glorious 19x10 master bath with DUAL showers, DUAL vanities, soaking tub, water closet, and huge master closet that connects through to the laundry room!  Guest room 1 features a walk-in closet and connects to the en-suite bath featuring dual vanities and separated shower/toilet.  The spacious laundry room has been upgraded with custom cabinetry for all your storage needs.  Two additional bedrooms and a bonus landing space complete the second story.  Huge unfinished basement includes rough-in plumbing, 9 foot ceilings, and room for at least 3 more bedrooms and/or family room/home gym, theater, etc.  Central A/C* Whole-house humidifier* Motorized window shades* Garage heater* Upgraded lighting* Fully irrigated lawn*  See full list of upgrades in MLS supplements - too many to list here!
